problem:
Find all values of the parameter \( b \) for which the system of equations

\[
\left\{
\begin{array}{l}
x^{2}-2x+y^{2}=0 \\
ax + y = ab
\end{array}
\right.
\]

has a solution for any \( a \).

Given two sets A and B defined as:
A = {x^2 + x + 1, -x, -x-1}
B = {-y, -y/2, y+1}
where x is a real number and y is a positive real number. If A = B, calculate the value of x^2 + y^2. Express your answer as a single integer.

Moving horizontally and vertically from point to point along the lines in the diagram below, how many routes are there from point  $A$  to point  $B$  which consist of six horizontal moves and six vertical moves?

[asy]
for(int i=0; i<=6;++i)
{
draw((i,i)--(6,i),black);
draw((i,i)--(i,0),black);
for(int a=i; a<=6;++a)
{
dot((a,i));
}
}
label("A",(0,0),W);
label("B",(6,6),N);

[/asy]

Let  $\alpha$  be the unique real root of the polynomial  $x^3-2x^2+x-1$ . It is known that  $1<\alpha<2$ . We define the sequence of polynomials  $\left\{{p_n(x)}\right\}_{n\ge0}$  by taking  $p_0(x)=x$  and setting
\begin{align*}
p_{n+1}(x)=(p_n(x))^2-\alpha
\end{align*}
How many distinct real roots does  $p_{10}(x)$  have?

